COLOUR (Fig. 75
A-D
): In life with body purple to vivid pink; paraterga and metaterga vivid pink to purple; surface below paraterga brownish pink or pink; head brown or blackish brown; antenna black or blackish brown (except distal part of antennomere 7 and antennomere 8 whitish); leg, sterna and epiproct pink; a few basal podomeres pale pink. Colour in alcohol: after 10-11 years changed brownish white, after 2-5 years changed to pale brown.

METATERGA (Fig. 76
A-C
): With 2 transverse rows of setiferous rose thorn-like spines; metaterga 2-18 with 2+2 anterior and 2+2 posterior spines; metatergum 19 with 2+2 anterior and 2+2 posterior spines/tubercles.

TELSON (Fig. 77
C-G
): Epiproct: tip slightly or moderately concave; lateral setiferous tubercles inconspicuous, short; apical tubercles conspicuous, usually short (very long and distinct in Kanchanaburi B population). Hypoproct trapeziform; caudal margin round, with inconspicuous setiferous tubercles.

LEGS (Fig. 77
H-J
): Very long and slender. Male femora 5 and 6 strongly humped ventrally in middle part.
